transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I see they've charged me for another shipment. I had canceled that.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me pull up your account, Marshall. Give me one second.

Speaker 2: Okay, can you just tell me your date of birth, please?

Speaker 1: 1-7-50.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much. I see you're a VIP status customer.

Speaker 1: Okay, I just pulled up tracking. That refill is going to be delivered to you today.

Speaker 2: So if you don't need it, don't open it up. Just write return to sender.

Speaker 1: Just write return to sender on the front.

Speaker 2: Pop it back in your mailbox. That way you don't have to pay for postage.

Speaker 1: And it already has a tracking number.

Speaker 2: And then...

Speaker 1: Can I just put it back in the mailbox?

Speaker 2: Yeah, just write return to sender and put it back in the mailbox.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And were you trying to order the AGV or did you order the generic on purpose?

Speaker 1: No, I ordered it, but not this...

Speaker 2: No, I didn't order it this time. The first time I did, I canceled it.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay.

Speaker 2: I didn't order it.

Speaker 1: Okay, okay.

Speaker 2: Did the doctor put you on monthly refills, which you do not need?

Speaker 1: No.

Speaker 2: But I see you ordered the generic Viagra and not the AGV.

Speaker 1: Is that what you wanted, the generic and not the AGV?

Speaker 2: The AGV is the latest formula.

Speaker 1: No, that's what I had. I ordered the latest formula the first time.

Speaker 2: No, you just...

Speaker 1: Remember the latest formula I had the first time?

Speaker 2: No, no, you ordered generic.

Speaker 1: It was supposed to be.

Speaker 2: No, I didn't order the generic.

Speaker 1: Okay, so what I'm going to do, I'm going to send you out a replacement free of charge

Speaker 2: to get you the correct AGV for your initial order.

Speaker 1: And then what I can do is I'll go ahead and pause your refills for six months.

Speaker 2: That way it allows the pharmacy to push through your replacement order.

Speaker 1: And then, you know, with your VIP status, a lot of people just like to pause it.

Speaker 2: That way it keeps your prescription active and just allows you to call in whenever you get a refill.

Speaker 1: Okay, okay, that sounds good.

Speaker 2: All right, perfect.

Speaker 1: So I just put return to send and put it in the mailbox, right?

Speaker 2: Correct, yes, perfect.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right, bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Thank you, gentlemen.

Speaker 1: All right.
